On the consumer front, if you've ordered alcohol online you may be in for a bit of a wait. Laurian Venter, the director of online retailer One-Day-Only chats to eNCA business anchor Devan Murugan about this. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Since that suspension on alcohol sales announced by President Cyril Ramaphosa on Sunday, more sectors in the value chain have responded with shock. Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize defended the ban saying that alcohol-related trauma cases were stifling hospitals and the country's COVID-19 medical response but warnings of job losses on wine farms, restaurants and other related sectors have been streaming in. READ: COVID-19 Regulations: Impact of alcohol sales ban On the consumer front, consumers that ordered alcohol online may be in for a bit of a wait. Online retailers say Sunday's sudden suspension of alcohol sales has compelled them to recall orders ready for delivery on Monday. “We have had to call back all deliveries of alcohol that had to go out this week,” said Laurian Venter, director of online retailer One-Day-Only. EXPLAINER: Why alcohol sales were suspended Venter says all stock has been safeguarded and will be delivered as soon as the lockdown ends. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.